Friday September 6th 2013 12:11 pm -04:00,Dont confuse frames with records  (I speak from personal experience) you get a frame for each function and there are multiple records within each frame. You need to count the frames not the records., Unresolved,0
Friday September 6th 2013 5:05 pm -04:00,If you step through the visualiser you can see that the definitions of the functions is part of the main procedure. However when those functions are called they open up a new frame in the stack with their own records which are then erased when the function is closed. If a function calls another function then multiple frames are opened. These are what need to be counted for the quiz., Unresolved,5
Saturday September 7th 2013 3:19 am -04:00,Once you understand what a frame is - and many people have been confused judging by some other threads - then if you step through the visualiser the answer is easy. A frame is created for the main procedure and also as each function is called. The frame will be labelled with the function name and contain at least one record. What the questions are trying to show is that some frames are erased and new ones created as the program progresses. , Unresolved,1
