Monday September 23rd 2013 3:00 pm -04:00,This is my tenth (or so) Coursera course and I see that this is a perennial problem for people who do not have the same reliability of internet and electricity that we take for granted in much of the west. Im afraid that I cant offer much hope for you as the whole Coursera model is based on having an Internet connection. If you want get a certificate then you need to ensure that you complete all the exercises and assignments in good time. It is actually feasible to get the certificate of completion even if you dont do the final exam providing that your other course work is of a high enough standard.If you really want/need to complete the final exam then you should take whatever steps possible to ensure that you have the most reliable connection possible or have a backup strategy. So I would suggest that you only attempt the exam at a time of day when you can be relatively confident of a continuous connection perhaps at night when others are asleep or when there is less demand on the local infrastructure. Make sure that you download and save as much as possible of the exam before attempting the questions so that you can work offline if necessary and upload when you regain a connection.  Also dont leave it until the last minute try and plan your time well in advance. I appreciate your concerns but these courses have so many students that making exceptions for a small minority is not fair for the majority. It sounds heartless I know but these courses are free and tailoring them to a minority of students in special circumstances is not a practical proposition.  So I wish you good luck and hope that you manage to complete the course without any problems., Resolved,6
