Tuesday September 24th 2013 10:33 am -04:00,Basically whatever is on the left of the = (assignment operator) gets the value of what is on the right. So to shift everything left you need to save the value of the lowest index and then let it equal whatever is contained in the next index higher. By doing this for every index everything is shifted one position to the left except for the highest index which is then assigned what was in the lowest index., Resolved,1
